<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Oil Pan, Vibration Damper, Oil
        Pump Water Pump, And Front Cover - Installation - Oil Pick-Up Tube
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Oil Pick-Up Tube</title>
        <figure id="f2050502" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg7/EG7554.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Oil Pick-Up Tube O-Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the O-ring on the oil pick-up tube mounting flange. If necessary, use a small amount
                of RTV sealant to hold the O-ring in place.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2050505" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figf13/F1308.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Oil Pick-Up Tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Pick-Up Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Support Bracket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bracket Nut</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the oil pick-up tube and mounting bolts. Tighten the bolts finger tight.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust the bracket at the main bearing cap stud and install the nut. Tighten the mounting
                bolts to the standard torque value after alignment. Tighten the bracket nut at the main bearing cap stud
                last.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
